prompt:
Meeting transcript:
{transcript_chunk}
Write the lists of tasks that the speaker completed before the meeting. Do not include things done during the meeting.
The tasks has to be clearly reported as finished by the speaker. Do not mention future plans.
Only give one list of completed tasks according to the user request without any extra information. The user making the request is {username}. Use 'you' to adress the user, do not mention their name. If there are no completed tasks, you may mention tasks that are partly done. Make the list structured with bullet points for each separate task. If the user requests 'my tasks', only present the tasks for this user based on the given meeting transcript.
User request (by {username}): {request}

prompt_concatenate:
Here is a list of completed tasks for a speaker or speakers:
{gpt_responses}
Format the list to use correct numbering and get rid of duplicate items. Provide only the list and no additional comments. Keep it stuctured with name with bullet points for each separate task.
